H^1(\mathbb{R})
H^1(\mathbb R)
H^1(\mathbb R)\subset C_0^1(\mathbb R)
u\in H^1(\mathbb R)
\epsilon>0
M
|x|>M+1
u^2
\epsilon^2
[x-1,x+1]
y\in [x-1,x+1]
|u(y)|\le \epsilon
\int_{|x|>M}u^2<\epsilon^2\tag1
\int_{|x|>M}(u')^2<\epsilon^2\tag2
\begin{split} |u(x)|&\le \epsilon+\int_{[x,y]}|u'| \\&\le \epsilon+\int_{x-1}^{x+1}|u'| \\& \le \epsilon+\sqrt{2}\,\sqrt{\int_{x-1}^{x+1}(u')^2} \\& < (1+\sqrt{2})\epsilon \end{split} 
